{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2017}} {{Use Indian English|date=June 2017}} {{Infobox recurring event | name = Ganga Pushkaram | native_name = | native_name_lang = te | logo = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | logo_size = 100px | image = File:Harkipauri panorama.jpg | image_size = 200px | alt = | caption = Pilgrims taking dip in the holy [[Ganges river]] at [[Haridwar]] (2012) | status = Active | genre = [[Hindu festivals]] | begins = | ends = | frequency = every 12 years | venue = {{Collapsible list |framestyle=border:none; padding:0; <!--Hides borders and improves row spacing--> |title=List of Major [[Ghats]] |1=[[Gangotri]]|2=Gangasagar|3=[[Haridwar]]|4=Badrinath|5=Kedarnath|6=Varanasi|7=[[Prayag]]}} | location = [[Ganga River]] | coordinates = | country = [[India]] | first = | founder_name = | last = 2011 | prev = | next = 22 April – 5 May 2023 | participants = | attendance = | capacity = | area = [[North India]] | budget = | activity = Holy river dip | leader_name = | patron = | organised = <!-- "organized=" also works --> | people = | member = | website = | footnotes = }}
'''Ganga Pushkaram''' is a festival of [[Ganga River|River Ganga]] normally occurs once in 12 years. This [[Pushkaram]] is observed for a period of 12 days from the time of entry of [[Jupiter]] into Aswini nakshatra ''Mesha'' rasi ([[Aries (astrology)|Aries]]).<ref>{{cite book |author=Roshen Dalal |title=Hinduism: An Alphabetical Guide |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zrk0AwAAQBAJ&pg=PT921 |date=18 April 2014 |publisher=Penguin Books Limited |isbn=978-81-8475-277-9 |pages=921–}}</ref>
