'''Sonon Asogli Thermal Power Station''', also '''Asogli Thermal Power Station''', is a {{convert|200|MW|abbr=on}} [[natural gas]]-fired thermal power station in [[Ghana]]. It is located in the Kpone neighborhood of the port city of [[Tema]], approximately {{convert|32|km|0}}, by road, east of the [[central business district]] of Ghana's capital city, [[Accra]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Globefeed.com (GFC)|accessdate=25 February 2016  |
url=http://distancecalculator.globefeed.com/Ghana_Distance_Result.asp?fromplace=Accra%2C%20Greater%20Accra%2C%20Ghana&toplace=Kpone%2C%20Tema%20Metropolitan%2C%20Greater%20Accra%2C%20Ghana%2C&dt1=ChIJc6e3soSQ3w8R0y0OZdhO0b4&dt2=ChIJ2TjJWVl-IBARMBy2Ly3x_lU|title=Distance between Accra, Greater Accra, Ghana and Kpone, Tema Metropolitan, Greater Accra, Ghana |last=GFC|
date=25 February 2016}}</ref>

The power plant, which came online in 2010, is privately owned by ''Sunon Asogli Power (Ghana) Limited''', a company in which ''Shenzhan Energy Group Limited'' maintains 60% shareholding and the remaining 40% is owned by ''China Africa Development Fund''.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=25 February 2016| url=https://www.modernghana.com/news/438732/1/asogli-power-plant-to-become-electricity-exporter-.html |title=Asogli Power Plant To Become Electricity Exporter By 2016|publisher=Modernghana.com Quoting CitiFMonline.com| last=General News |date=9 January 2013|location=Accra}}</ref> Installed capacity is 200MW, although often, output is less than maximum.<ref>{{cite web|title=Asogli Power in Ghana resumes power generation| url=http://constructionreviewonline.com/2015/06/asogli-power-ghana-resumes-power-generation/|accessdate=25 February 2016|date=12 June 2015|last=CRO|publisher=Construction Review Online (CRO)}}</ref>

